 against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223037","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223037","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B62AC-6E2A-1014-B4B0-C0F8630A936A","group_id_src":"V-223037","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223037r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:568","href":"U_M