_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223038","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223038","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B666A-6E2A-1014-BA4A-9B8E45B32051","group_id_src":"V-223038","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223038r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:578","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223039","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223039","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B6A66-6E2A-1014-9BD8-A885DB3B2A6B","group_id_src":"V-223039","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:572","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ to âEnabledâ.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223040","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223040","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B6E96-6E2A-1014-B74A-AA7C4AB59CAF","group_id_src":"V-223040","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:574","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223041","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223041","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B7294-6E2A-1014-9F13-952810031A22","group_id_src":"V-223041","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:575","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as âexpiredâ, ârevokedâ, or âname mismatchâ errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001954"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223042","title":"SRG-APP-000427"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223042","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B767E-6E2A-1014-8A12-C0B8A6843659","group_id_src":"V-223042","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:577","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223043","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223043","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B7A55-6E2A-1014-AFF3-93230A3A58AC","group_id_src":"V-223043","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:576","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223044","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223044","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B7E02-6E2A-1014-9FE2-E4AD4A75F05F","group_id_src":"V-223044","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:579","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223045","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223045","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B8E42-6E2A-1014-A8D3-83835E91B3C5","group_id_src":"V-223045","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:573","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223046","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223046","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B95C7-6E2A-1014-8B74-8BF2BA870E97","group_id_src":"V-223046","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:585","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to âEnabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled is set to 0)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223048","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223048","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645B9E86-6E2A-1014-9421-CE0775324309","group_id_src":"V-223048","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:586","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to âDisabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled is set to 1)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223049","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223049","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BA313-6E2A-1014-AD9C-94FEAEC998EE","group_id_src":"V-223049","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:583","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Pane &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223050","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223050","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BA787-6E2A-1014-B717-EFA6E7D3A1A5","group_id_src":"V-223050","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223050r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:436","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223051","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223051","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BAC21-6E2A-1014-8791-9A3F603EBF26","group_id_src":"V-223051","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:584","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users wonât be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223052","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223052","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BB20F-6E2A-1014-834F-EF1F5BE68CE3","group_id_src":"V-223052","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223052r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:588","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223053","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223053","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BB6C1-6E2A-1014-ACC4-C2A5DCD1F5BB","group_id_src":"V-223053","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:437","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223054","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223054","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BBB28-6E2A-1014-ADCB-B46B7476D216","group_id_src":"V-223054","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:589","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone-&gt;'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223055","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223055","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BBFB0-6E2A-1014-B835-9F07A260FE04","group_id_src":"V-223055","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:591","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ must be âEnabledâ. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ to âEnabledâ.","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Developer Tools are disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223056","title":"SRG-APP-000266"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223056","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BC458-6E2A-1014-9F6A-9348E05C5A43","group_id_src":"V-223056","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:438","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223057","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223057","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BC8BF-6E2A-1014-89A2-9C1733D7376C","group_id_src":"V-223057","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223057r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:439","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run ActiveX controls and plugins)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223058","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223058","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BCD4E-6E2A-1014-91E5-83CF9994BD85","group_id_src":"V-223058","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:440","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223059","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223059","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BD1A4-6E2A-1014-B109-96BAF6175A6A","group_id_src":"V-223059","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223059r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:441","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow file downloads)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223060","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223060","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BD5E5-6E2A-1014-85C4-A4BC61C76434","group_id_src":"V-223060","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:453","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223061","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223061","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BDB36-6E2A-1014-A34E-F912706C85C9","group_id_src":"V-223061","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:443","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223062","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223062","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BE017-6E2A-1014-A0ED-FDC43C8D0DD3","group_id_src":"V-223062","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:444","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow META REFRESH)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223063","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223063","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BE4DD-6E2A-1014-A90A-A749FC886431","group_id_src":"V-223063","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:445","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223064","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223064","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BE996-6E2A-1014-82BA-ECB939F6CA06","group_id_src":"V-223064","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223064r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:447","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223065","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223065","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BF177-6E2A-1014-80C6-9C2CAF6883C4","group_id_src":"V-223065","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223065r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:448","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223066","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223066","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BF62D-6E2A-1014-81BC-A8F5796546FF","group_id_src":"V-223066","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:449","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Userdata persistence)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223067","title":"SRG-APP-000231"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223067","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645BFA86-6E2A-1014-B839-815FC503FDE3","group_id_src":"V-223067","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223067r961128"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:450","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow active scripting)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223068","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223068","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C019D-6E2A-1014-A894-9076B58696DA","group_id_src":"V-223068","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:451","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223069","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223069","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C0A48-6E2A-1014-9C3E-ABB0E8D60825","group_id_src":"V-223069","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:452","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Logon options)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223070","title":"SRG-APP-000219"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223070","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C1031-6E2A-1014-B284-A61D2F114458","group_id_src":"V-223070","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:513","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Disable Configuring History must be Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\40 entered in Days to keep pages in History)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223071","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223071","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C147C-6E2A-1014-9D94-8A5934FFC4E7","group_id_src":"V-223071","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223071r960879"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:419","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Add/Delete Sites)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223072","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223072","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C18D0-6E2A-1014-8DAC-810D07D111B9","group_id_src":"V-223072","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:418","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Change Policies)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223073","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223073","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C1CEF-6E2A-1014-B8B7-F9B3BB4585EB","group_id_src":"V-223073","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:417","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. ","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Use Only Machine Settings)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223074","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223074","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C210E-6E2A-1014-9810-976EDDDBA7C7","group_id_src":"V-223074","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:457","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn off the Security Settings Check feature)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223075","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223075","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C2565-6E2A-1014-A146-A0607FD433B8","group_id_src":"V-223075","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:459","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. ","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Allow Software to Run or Install Even if the Signature is Invalid)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223076","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223076","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C29EA-6E2A-1014-B5D3-F49C89FD1C03","group_id_src":"V-223076","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:564","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223077","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223077","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C30C9-6E2A-1014-B5D3-B71C08E4C72D","group_id_src":"V-223077","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:461","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Server Certificate Revocation)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223078","title":"SRG-APP-000175"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223078","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C35B2-6E2A-1014-924D-8D6E6FEF1305","group_id_src":"V-223078","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:462","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Signature on Downloaded Programs)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001749"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223079","title":"SRG-APP-000131"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223079","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C3C89-6E2A-1014-A71B-856AE99DFA48","group_id_src":"V-223079","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:463","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs))\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223080","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223080","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C41D7-6E2A-1014-AAF0-B2F42BCA7B39","group_id_src":"V-223080","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:464","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223081","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223081","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C46C4-6E2A-1014-95E8-B5FE97FE6C87","group_id_src":"V-223081","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:465","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223082","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223082","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C4BFD-6E2A-1014-BA0A-A4854E014B86","group_id_src":"V-223082","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:466","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223083","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223083","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C50ED-6E2A-1014-8536-DAF3FA39D52C","group_id_src":"V-223083","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:467","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223084","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223084","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C5601-6E2A-1014-88EA-B9C935A8A154","group_id_src":"V-223084","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:468","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223085","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223085","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C5AEE-6E2A-1014-AA53-EEB55EFC1C0B","group_id_src":"V-223085","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:567","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt;Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223086","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223086","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C60F2-6E2A-1014-ABFC-808921E0F799","group_id_src":"V-223086","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:469","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223087","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223087","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C6613-6E2A-1014-B306-F4B626931FAD","group_id_src":"V-223087","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:470","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223088","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223088","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C6A9E-6E2A-1014-80C8-E9D2660C61C4","group_id_src":"V-223088","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223088r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:471","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223089","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223089","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C6EF7-6E2A-1014-9A0F-CB19B0B61420","group_id_src":"V-223089","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:473","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223090","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223090","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C7360-6E2A-1014-8505-8DDAA6E4A743","group_id_src":"V-223090","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:474","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Loose or un-compiled XAML files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223091","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223091","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C7862-6E2A-1014-A476-8405CC110F6E","group_id_src":"V-223091","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:475","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Loose XAML files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223092","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223092","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C7CE6-6E2A-1014-9717-E8BC9AFC6112","group_id_src":"V-223092","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223092r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:480","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223093","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223093","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C817C-6E2A-1014-B686-F32A2801437E","group_id_src":"V-223093","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:481","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223094","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223094","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C85D2-6E2A-1014-B3B5-F0ADD97C1A3E","group_id_src":"V-223094","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:482","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223095","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223095","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C8C20-6E2A-1014-A564-9F2E1B174AC7","group_id_src":"V-223095","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:483","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223096","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223096","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C90C3-6E2A-1014-A18C-DAF4128D05CA","group_id_src":"V-223096","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:484","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223097","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223097","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C9502-6E2A-1014-92A6-E3975E25C7B5","group_id_src":"V-223097","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:485","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223098","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223098","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C9936-6E2A-1014-8312-F24A0EA86031","group_id_src":"V-223098","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:486","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow binary and script behaviors)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223099","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223099","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645C9D41-6E2A-1014-8955-82EB0F7C65B4","group_id_src":"V-223099","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223099r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:487","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223100","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223100","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CA12B-6E2A-1014-87EB-9B07AE1784B6","group_id_src":"V-223100","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:488","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223101","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223101","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CA548-6E2A-1014-9038-DC5508C6FFEC","group_id_src":"V-223101","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:502","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223102","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223102","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CA973-6E2A-1014-8294-B74C9C8F84B7","group_id_src":"V-223102","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:503","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223103","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223103","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CAD87-6E2A-1014-8367-9A004BE256BB","group_id_src":"V-223103","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:489","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223104","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223104","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CB19F-6E2A-1014-8C27-92826901FEB0","group_id_src":"V-223104","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:510","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59581","V-46717"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223105","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223105","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CB55B-6E2A-1014-976D-A10F0F8061BE","group_id_src":"V-223105","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:511","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223106","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223106","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CB941-6E2A-1014-AF74-BC1C2D47B4CF","group_id_src":"V-223106","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223106r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:504","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223107","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223107","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CBD0D-6E2A-1014-BA87-F14AAFE72B1C","group_id_src":"V-223107","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:490","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223108","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223108","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CC0C9-6E2A-1014-9DCB-B691A2D2B01C","group_id_src":"V-223108","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:491","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223109","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223109","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CC4FB-6E2A-1014-ACBA-A4255E79EA4F","group_id_src":"V-223109","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:492","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223110","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223110","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CC8C1-6E2A-1014-8327-8936BD1648B8","group_id_src":"V-223110","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:505","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223111","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223111","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CCC70-6E2A-1014-ADE3-FD6AF0284DA2","group_id_src":"V-223111","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223111r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:506","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223112","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223112","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CD044-6E2A-1014-BC98-A6EF4F0D2340","group_id_src":"V-223112","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:493","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\ Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223113","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223113","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CD3E6-6E2A-1014-98E6-DEFC1670F3C8","group_id_src":"V-223113","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:494","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223114","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223114","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CDA00-6E2A-1014-8B25-EBE1D580C772","group_id_src":"V-223114","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:495","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223115","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223115","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CDDFD-6E2A-1014-BDA2-FEBF9CD4658A","group_id_src":"V-223115","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223115r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:496","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223116","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223116","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CE1FF-6E2A-1014-AE70-EA846466EA4A","group_id_src":"V-223116","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223116r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:507","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223117","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223117","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CE5CC-6E2A-1014-9762-C5758AD1A3E3","group_id_src":"V-223117","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:508","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223118","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223118","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CE99F-6E2A-1014-ADEE-CBBC01680D61","group_id_src":"V-223118","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:497","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223119","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223119","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CED85-6E2A-1014-ABD3-AE31C242EC10","group_id_src":"V-223119","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:498","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223120","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223120","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CF168-6E2A-1014-8C73-95226E07CC91","group_id_src":"V-223120","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:499","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Scripting of Java applets)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223121","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223121","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CF547-6E2A-1014-BED8-A9BA21C554F2","group_id_src":"V-223121","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223121r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223122","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223122","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223122","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CF912-6E2A-1014-814F-BA227A766532","group_id_src":"V-223122","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:509","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn Off Crash Detection)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223123","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223123","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645CFCF5-6E2A-1014-A9A4-E5FD76D01B4D","group_id_src":"V-223123","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223124","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223124","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223124","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D00BF-6E2A-1014-AB67-C8849DD29E34","group_id_src":"V-223124","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:514","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223125","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223125","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D049F-6E2A-1014-9806-B6871D9E83F9","group_id_src":"V-223125","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:516","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Configure Delete Browsing History on exit)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223126","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223126","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D08B3-6E2A-1014-95E1-969BE229F427","group_id_src":"V-223126","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223126r960879"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:517","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223127","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223127","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D0C71-6E2A-1014-84D5-E48E1617EC8F","group_id_src":"V-223127","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:518","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\InPrivate\\Turn off InPrivate Browsing)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223128","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223128","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D1040-6E2A-1014-A35D-8142A39B87A7","group_id_src":"V-223128","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223128r960864"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:519","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223129","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223129","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D141F-6E2A-1014-96CD-D50DB80ECAE0","group_id_src":"V-223129","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:520","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223130","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223130","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D17FA-6E2A-1014-9BD4-DA2C74A2FAE9","group_id_src":"V-223130","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223130r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:541","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223131","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223131","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D1BEE-6E2A-1014-896C-B6A10A8ED173","group_id_src":"V-223131","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:521","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223132","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223132","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D1FED-6E2A-1014-BA91-B3AF0BD8BB59","group_id_src":"V-223132","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:542","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223133","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223133","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D2573-6E2A-1014-A985-810251228141","group_id_src":"V-223133","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:522","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223134","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223134","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D2ABE-6E2A-1014-84EA-F2217E18DFA8","group_id_src":"V-223134","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:543","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223135","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223135","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D2E77-6E2A-1014-ABA9-A883608DE813","group_id_src":"V-223135","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:523","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter must be Enabled and Enable selected)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223136","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223136","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D3237-6E2A-1014-B793-F54BAD86881C","group_id_src":"V-223136","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223136r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:524","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223137","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223137","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D35EC-6E2A-1014-9294-8E8BB2512FC8","group_id_src":"V-223137","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223137r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:525","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223138","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223138","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D39A3-6E2A-1014-87C6-D96999614AE1","group_id_src":"V-223138","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:526","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223139","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223139","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D3D56-6E2A-1014-8E3C-B74EA25DE022","group_id_src":"V-223139","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:527","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223140","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223140","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D4106-6E2A-1014-9EA4-E8604CBC117F","group_id_src":"V-223140","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:528","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223141","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223141","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D44A7-6E2A-1014-803F-9C340BDA7749","group_id_src":"V-223141","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:529","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223142","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223142","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D484F-6E2A-1014-A867-E81E13DAE70F","group_id_src":"V-223142","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:530","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disable selected)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223143","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223143","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D4D66-6E2A-1014-B8B6-B75E4D7D8DF9","group_id_src":"V-223143","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223143r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:531","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223144","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223144","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D5186-6E2A-1014-9E63-DC3F47931DE8","group_id_src":"V-223144","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:532","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223145","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223145","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D5540-6E2A-1014-96C0-9ABBCDDA52C2","group_id_src":"V-223145","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223145r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:533","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223146","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223146","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D58F4-6E2A-1014-A9F0-F51DFF156335","group_id_src":"V-223146","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223146r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:534","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disabled selected)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223147","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223147","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D5CB5-6E2A-1014-923E-D44BD8FD63FA","group_id_src":"V-223147","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:556","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","comments":null,"check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Advanced Page/Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode )\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223148","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223148","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D6097-6E2A-1014-AFA9-853591ACD05A","group_id_src":"V-223148","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:547","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223149","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-223149","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D644D-6E2A-1014-A098-EE70E2FB12F9","group_id_src":"V-223149","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:580","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('turn off encryption support' setting is handled by Group Policy.)\nTest            :   true (TLS 1.2 must be selected for the IE option 'turn off encryption support' via Group Policy.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-250540","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-250540","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D682E-6E2A-1014-8DAA-D0F206943B55","group_id_src":"V-250540","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:581","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Allow insecure fallback for:' set to 'No Sites')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-250541","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-250541","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D6D94-6E2A-1014-B485-DC029F98D1CF","group_id_src":"V-250541","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.win:def:252910","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","comments":null,"check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor.\n\nIf Internet Explorer 11 is installed, this is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Remove the Internet Explorer 11 application.","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","stig_uuid":"644C1466-6E2A-1014-A608-B505CB188F18","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Internet Explorer 11 is installed)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-252910","title":"SRG-APP-000456"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-252910","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1156566_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"645D726A-6E2A-1014-ACB1-FA4B1D421261","group_id_src":"V-252910","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-252910r1156566"}],"size":137,"version":"2"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","stig_id":"MS_Defender_Antivirus","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","stig_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus","uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","rules":[{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:1","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89827","V-75147"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000279","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; \"Configure detection for potentially unwanted applications\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nIf the value \"PUAProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; \"Configure Detection for Potentially Unwanted Applications\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Block\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000001","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"After enabling this feature, PUA protection blocking takes effect on endpoint clients after the next signature update or computer restart. Signature updates take place daily under typical circumstances. PUA will be blocked and automatically quarantined.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Configure detection for potentially unwanted applications is set to 'Enabled' and 'Block')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block the Potentially Unwanted Application (PUA) feature.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001243"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213426","title":"SRG-APP-000279"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213426","rule_id_src":"SV-213426r961197_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD1819-6E2A-1014-AAFC-DD369CFA0699","group_id_src":"V-213426","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213426r961197"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:2","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89831","V-75151"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000279","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; \"Turn off routine remediation\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRoutinelyTakingAction\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; \"Turn off routine remediation\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000003","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows Microsoft Defender configuration to automatically take action on all detected threats. The action to be taken on a particular threat is determined by the combination of the policy-defined action user-defined action and the signature-defined action. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender does not automatically take action on the detected threats but prompts users to choose from the actions available for each threat. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender automatically takes action on all detected threats after a nonconfigurable delay of approximately five seconds.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Turn off routine remediation)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to automatically take action on all detected tasks.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001243"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213427","title":"SRG-APP-000279"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213427","rule_id_src":"SV-213427r961197_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD1F20-6E2A-1014-A37C-BBE68450BA1C","group_id_src":"V-213427","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213427r961197"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:3","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89833","V-75153"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Windows Defender Antivirus\" is set to âNot Configuredâ.\n\nFor Windows 10:\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAntiSpyware\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"For Windows 10: Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus \"Turn off Microsoft Defender Antivirus\" to \"Not Configured\". \n","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000004","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting turns off Microsoft Defender Antivirus. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus does not run and computers are not scanned for malware or other potentially unwanted software. \n\nWhen the setting is disabled and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, the two applications can both simultaneously try to protect the system. The two AV solutions both attempt to quarantine the same threat and will fight for access to delete the file. Users will see conflicts and the system may lock up until the two solutions finish processing. \n\nWhen the setting is not configured and a third-party antivirus solution is installed, both applications coexist on the system without conflicts.  Defender Antivirus will automatically disable itself and will enable if the third-party solution stops functioning.  When the setting is not configured and Defender Antivirus is the only AV solution, Defender AV will run (default state) and receive definition updates. An administrator account is needed to turn off the service. A standard user cannot disable the service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Micrsoft Defender Antivirus\\Turn off Windows Defender Antivirus)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to run and scan for malware and other potentially unwanted software.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213428","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213428","rule_id_src":"SV-213428r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD245D-6E2A-1014-8579-F2AC6742C288","group_id_src":"V-213428","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213428r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:4","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89835","V-75155"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Path Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured.\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n \nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Paths\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Path Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000005","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for files under the paths specified or for the fully qualified resources specified. Paths should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of a path or a fully qualified resource name. As an example, a path might be defined as: \"c:\\Windows\" to exclude all files in this directory. A fully qualified resource name might be defined as: \"C:\\Windows\\App.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.\n\nExceptions can be made to allow file/folders that are impacting enterprise applications to be excluded from being scanned. All exclusions should be documented and approved.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Exclusions\\Path Exclusions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files for scanning.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213429","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213429","rule_id_src":"SV-213429r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD293B-6E2A-1014-AE79-E653B443CC73","group_id_src":"V-213429","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213429r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:5","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89837","V-75157"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Process Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"Exclusions_Processes\" does not exist, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft  Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Process Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000006","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the disabling of scheduled and real-time scanning for any file opened by any of the specified processes. The process itself will not be excluded. To exclude the process, use the Path exclusion. Processes should be added under the options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair where the name should be a string representation of the path to the process image. Note that only executables can be excluded. For example, a process might be defined as: \"c:\\windows\\app.exe\". The value is not used and it is recommended that this be set to 0.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Exclusions\\Process Exclusions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not exclude files opened by specified processes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213430","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213430","rule_id_src":"SV-213430r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD2E0D-6E2A-1014-B244-AE89F5795ECA","group_id_src":"V-213430","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213430r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:6","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89839","V-75159"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Exclusions\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableAutoExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Exclusions &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Auto Exclusions\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000007","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting allows an administrator to specify if Automatic Exclusions feature for Server SKUs should be turned off.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Exclusions\\Turn off Auto Exclusions)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable the Automatic Exclusions feature.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213431","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213431","rule_id_src":"SV-213431r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD3292-6E2A-1014-A773-CA09B24C6E7C","group_id_src":"V-213431","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213431r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:7","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89841","V-75161"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideSpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000008","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to join Microsoft MAPS. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\MAPS\\Configure local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to disable local setting override for reporting to Microsoft MAPS.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213432","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213432","rule_id_src":"SV-213432r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD36D9-6E2A-1014-8F63-F9D2466BA9B3","group_id_src":"V-213432","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213432r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:8","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89843","V-75163"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBlockAtFirstSeen\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft  Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Configure the 'Block at First Sight' feature\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000009","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This feature ensures the device checks in real time with the Microsoft Active Protection Service (MAPS) before allowing certain content to be run or accessed. If this feature is disabled, the check will not occur, which will lower the protection state of the device. \n\nEnabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned on. \nDisabled - The Block at First Sight setting is turned off. \n\nThis feature requires these Group Policy settings to be set as follows: \nMAPS &gt;&gt; The \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nMAPS &gt;&gt; The \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" should be set to 1 (Send safe samples) or 3 (Send all samples). Setting to 0 (Always Prompt) will lower the protection state of the device. Setting to 2 (Never send) means the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection &gt;&gt; The \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" policy must be enabled or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function. \nReal-time Protection &gt;&gt; Do not enable the \"Turn off real-time protection\" policy or the \"Block at First Sight\" feature will not function.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\MAPS\\Configure the Block at First Sight)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check in real time with MAPS before content is run or accessed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213433","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213433","rule_id_src":"SV-213433r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD3D53-6E2A-1014-A58A-A61DF1806435","group_id_src":"V-213433","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213433r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:213434","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89847","V-75167"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems, this is Not Applicable.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Advanced MAPS\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SpynetReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, or REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is Not Applicable.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Join Microsoft MAPS\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Basic MAPS\" or \"Advanced MAPS\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000010","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows joining Microsoft MAPS. Microsoft MAPS is the online community that helps in choosing how to respond to potential threats. The community also helps stop the spread of new malicious software infections. You can choose to send basic or additional information about detected software. Additional information helps Microsoft create new definitions and protect your computer. This information can include things like location of detected items on your computer if harmful software was removed. The information will be automatically collected and sent. In some instances personal information might unintentionally be sent to Microsoft. However Microsoft will not use this information to identify you or contact you. \n\nPossible options are: \n(0x0) Disabled (default) \n(0x1) Basic membership \n(0x2) Advanced membership \n\nBasic membership will send basic information to Microsoft about software that has been detected, including where the software came from, the actions that you apply or that are applied automatically, and whether the actions were successful. Advanced membership will send, in addition to basic information, more information to Microsoft about malicious software spyware and potentially unwanted software, including the location of the software file names, how the software operates, and how it has impacted your computer. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, you will join Microsoft MAPS with the membership specified. If this setting is disabled or do not configured, you will not join Microsoft MAPS. In Windows 10, Basic membership is no longer available, so setting the value to 1 or 2 enrolls the device into Advanced membership.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (SpynetReporting == 1 or 2)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must join Microsoft MAPS.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213434","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213434","rule_id_src":"SV-213434r1134051_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD4275-6E2A-1014-8BE5-87CF71C5AC7E","group_id_src":"V-213434","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213434r1134051"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:10","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89887","V-75207"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Send safe samples\" is selected from the drop-down box.\n     \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Spynet\n\nCriteria: If the value \"SubmitSamplesConsent\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. For other systems this is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MAPS &gt;&gt; \"Send file samples when further analysis is required\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Send safe samples\" from the drop-down box.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000011","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures behavior of samples submission when opt-in for MAPS telemetry is set. Possible options are:  \n(0x0) Always prompt\n(0x1) Send safe samples automatically \n(0x2) Never send  \n(0x3) Send all samples automatically","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\MAPS\\Send file samples when further analysis is required)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to only send safe samples for MAPS telemetry.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213435","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213435","rule_id_src":"SV-213435r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD46BE-6E2A-1014-A64F-FE3B8113245B","group_id_src":"V-213435","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213435r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:11","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89889","V-75209"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Network Inspection System &gt;&gt; \"Turn on protocol recognition\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableProtocolRecognition\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Network Inspection System &gt;&gt; \"Turn on protocol recognition\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000012","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of protocol recognition for network protection against exploits of known vulnerabilities. If this setting is enabled or not configured, protocol recognition will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, protocol recognition will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Network Inspection System\\Turn on protocol recognition)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for protocol recognition for network protection.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213436","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213436","rule_id_src":"SV-213436r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD4AFB-6E2A-1014-96CE-83D05A46BA37","group_id_src":"V-213436","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213436r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:12","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89891","V-75211"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000013","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for file and program activity on your computer. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Real-time Protection/Configure local setting override for monitoring file and program activity on your computer is set to Disabled or Not Configured)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow local override of monitoring for file and program activity.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213437","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213437","rule_id_src":"SV-213437r960921_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD4EF8-6E2A-1014-8D8E-87A4342EDC53","group_id_src":"V-213437","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213437r960921"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:13","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89893","V-75213"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideRealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000014","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Real-time Protection/Configure local setting override for monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity is set to Disabled or Not Configured)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of monitoring for incoming and outgoing file activity.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213438","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213438","rule_id_src":"SV-213438r960921_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD5316-6E2A-1014-BA44-8649A14CC6C0","group_id_src":"V-213438","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213438r960921"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:14","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89895","V-75215"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000015","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Real-time Protection/Configure local setting override for scanning all downloaded files and attachments is set to Disabled or Not Configured)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of scanning for downloaded files and attachments.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213439","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213439","rule_id_src":"SV-213439r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD588A-6E2A-1014-8436-DC4C9C155B34","group_id_src":"V-213439","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213439r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:15","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89897","V-75217"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000016","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration of behavior monitoring. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Real-time Protection/Configure local setting override for turn on behavior monitoring is set to Disabled or Not Configured)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to not allow override of behavior monitoring.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213440","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213440","rule_id_src":"SV-213440r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD5CB0-6E2A-1014-AD53-E461439B340C","group_id_src":"V-213440","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213440r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:16","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89899","V-75219"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"LocalSettingOverrideDisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000017","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures a local override for the configuration to turn on real-time protection. This setting can only be set by Group Policy. If this setting is enabled, the local preference setting will take priority over Group Policy. If this setting is disabled or not configured, Group Policy will take priority over the local preference setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Configure local setting override to turn on real-time protection)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV Group Policy settings must take priority over the local preference settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213441","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213441","rule_id_src":"SV-213441r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD6308-6E2A-1014-B78F-D1F0F2351ABA","group_id_src":"V-213441","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213441r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:17","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89901","V-75221"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" is set to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RealtimeScanDirection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1 or 2, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity\" to \"Enabled\" with a policy option value of \"bi-directional (full on-access)\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000018","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of monitoring for incoming and outgoing files without having to turn off monitoring entirely. It is recommended for use on servers that have a lot of incoming and outgoing file activity but for performance reasons need to have scanning disabled for a particular scan direction. The appropriate configuration should be evaluated based on the server role. Note that this configuration is only honored for NTFS volumes. For any other file system type, full monitoring of file and program activity will be present on those volumes. \n\nThe options for this setting are mutually exclusive: \n0 = Scan incoming and outgoing files (default) \n1 = Scan incoming files only \n2 = Scan outgoing files only \n\nAny other value, or if the value does not exist, resolves to the default (0). If this setting is enabled, the specified type of monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, monitoring for incoming and outgoing files will be enabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Configure monitoring for incoming and outgoing file and program activity)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must monitor for incoming and outgoing files.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213442","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213442","rule_id_src":"SV-213442r1144028_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD680F-6E2A-1014-B8CF-8A36E239A552","group_id_src":"V-213442","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213442r1144028"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:18","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89903","V-75223"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer to be scanned\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableOnAccessProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Monitor file and program activity on your computer\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000019","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of monitoring for file and program activity. If this setting is enabled or not configured, monitoring for file and program activity will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, monitoring for file and program activity will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Monitor file and program activity on your computer' is set to 'Enabled' or 'Not Configured')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to monitor for file and program activity.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213443","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213443","rule_id_src":"SV-213443r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD6C30-6E2A-1014-8326-E36298BCC770","group_id_src":"V-213443","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213443r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:19","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89905","V-75225"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableIOAVProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Scan all downloaded files and attachments\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000020","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of scanning for all downloaded files and attachments. If this setting is enabled or not configured, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, scanning for all downloaded files and attachments will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Scan all downloaded files and attachments)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan all downloaded files and attachments.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213444","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213444","rule_id_src":"SV-213444r961089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD7046-6E2A-1014-B009-EEFF5F9C30EC","group_id_src":"V-213444","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213444r961089"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:20","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89907","V-75227"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn off real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn off real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000021","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting turns off real-time protection prompts for known malware detection. Microsoft Defender Antivirus alerts  when malware or potentially unwanted software attempts to install itself or to run on your computer. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will not prompt users to take actions on malware detections. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will prompt users to take actions on malware detections.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn off real-time protection)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213445","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213445","rule_id_src":"SV-213445r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD7451-6E2A-1014-A317-91A82DBF042F","group_id_src":"V-213445","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213445r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:21","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89909","V-75229"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000022","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of behavior monitoring. If this setting is enabled or not configured, behavior monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, behavior monitoring will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn on behavior monitoring)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213446","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213446","rule_id_src":"SV-213446r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD7871-6E2A-1014-847B-8DE7995D9818","group_id_src":"V-213446","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213446r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:22","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89911","V-75231"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000023","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of process scanning when real-time protection is turned on. This helps to catch malware, which could start when real-time protection is turned off. If this setting is enabled or not configured, a process scan will be initiated when real-time protection is turned on. If this setting is disabled, a process scan will not be initiated when real-time protection is turned on.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213447","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213447","rule_id_src":"SV-213447r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD7C6D-6E2A-1014-B997-8BC05D4B1AF2","group_id_src":"V-213447","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213447r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:23","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89913","V-75233"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan archive files\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableArchiveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan archive files\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000024","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of scans for malicious software and unwanted software in archive files such as .ZIP or .CAB files. If this setting is enabled or not configured, archive files will be scanned. If this setting is disabled, archive files will not be scanned.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Scan archive files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213448","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213448","rule_id_src":"SV-213448r961194_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD8024-6E2A-1014-B39B-BED35A754A07","group_id_src":"V-213448","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213448r961194"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:24","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89915","V-75235"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan removable drives\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRemovableDriveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan removable drives\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000025","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether or not to scan for malicious software and unwanted software in the contents of removable drives such as USB flash drives when running a full scan. If this setting is enabled, removable drives will be scanned during any type of scan. If this setting is disabled or not configured, removable drives will not be scanned during a full scan. Removable drives may still be scanned during quick scan and custom scan.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Scan removable drives)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000870"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213449","title":"SRG-APP-000073"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213449","rule_id_src":"SV-213449r960852_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD8424-6E2A-1014-89F3-AA40761D5663","group_id_src":"V-213449","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213449r960852"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:25","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89917","V-75237"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000277","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" is set to \"Enabled\" and anything other than \"Never\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0x8, this is a finding.\n\nValues of 0x0 through 0x7 are acceptable and not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" to \"Enabled \" and select anything other than \"Never\" in the drop-down box.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000026","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to perform a scheduled scan. The scan can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day  \n(0x1) Sunday  \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never (default)  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, a scheduled scan will run at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, a scheduled scan will run at a default frequency.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001241"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213450","title":"SRG-APP-000277"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213450","rule_id_src":"SV-213450r961191_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD8902-6E2A-1014-8870-C5A2541899A4","group_id_src":"V-213450","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213450r961191"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:26","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89919","V-75239"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableEmailScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000027","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of e-mail scanning. When e-mail scanning is enabled, the engine will parse the mailbox and mail files according to their specific format in order to analyze the mail bodies and attachments. Several e-mail formats are currently supported, for example: pst (Outlook), dbx mbx mime (Outlook Express), binhex (Mac). If this setting is enabled, e-mail scanning will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, e-mail scanning will be disabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Scan/Turn on e-mail scanning is set to Enabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213451","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213451","rule_id_src":"SV-213451r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD8D7E-6E2A-1014-9C5C-9BA2862C8521","group_id_src":"V-213451","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213451r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:27","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89921","V-75241"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before spyware security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antispyware is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender AV spyware age requirement will be NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ASSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000028","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before spyware definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date_less than 7)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date_not 0)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001240"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213452","title":"SRG-APP-000276"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213452","rule_id_src":"SV-213452r961188_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD918B-6E2A-1014-B69E-A1D4D2D41C48","group_id_src":"V-213452","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213452r961188"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:28","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89923","V-75243"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt;Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before virus security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antivirus protection is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender Antivirus age requirement is NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AVSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000029","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before virus definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default, this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date_less than 7)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date_not 0)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001240"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213453","title":"SRG-APP-000276"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213453","rule_id_src":"SV-213453r961188_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD9596-6E2A-1014-9937-C43E65E790B4","group_id_src":"V-213453","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213453r961188"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:29","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89925","V-75245"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000261","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to check for security intelligence updates\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Every Day\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Every Day\" in the drop-down box.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000030","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to check for definition updates. The check can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day (default)  \n(0x1) Sunday   \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, the check for definition updates will occur at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, the check for definition updates will occur at a default frequency.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001308"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213454","title":"SRG-APP-000261"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213454","rule_id_src":"SV-213454r961161_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD9980-6E2A-1014-8302-F7D8E0DF4D59","group_id_src":"V-213454","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213454r961161"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:30","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89927","V-75247"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the âShowâ¦â box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"5\" and the \"Value\" field  contains \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.\n","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"5\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000031","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Severe)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213455","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213455","rule_id_src":"SV-213455r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBD9D59-6E2A-1014-9FCB-8270EA39C4C4","group_id_src":"V-213455","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213455r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:31","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92661","V-77965"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000032","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This rule blocks the following file types from being run or launched from an email seen in either Microsoft Outlook or webmail (such as Gmail.com or Outlook.com):\nExecutable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr)\nScript files (such as a PowerShell .ps, VisualBasic .vbs, or JavaScript .js file)\nScript archive files","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules550)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213456","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213456","rule_id_src":"SV-213456r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDA11C-6E2A-1014-8E21-B172A34C9043","group_id_src":"V-213456","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213456r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:32","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92663","V-77967"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000033","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word or Excel, will not be allowed to create child processes. This is a typical malware behavior, especially for macro-based attacks that attempt to use Office apps to launch or download malicious executables.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213457","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213457","rule_id_src":"SV-213457r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDA4C4-6E2A-1014-BB82-FCB1ABE694E4","group_id_src":"V-213457","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213457r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:33","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92665","V-77969"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\nValue:  1\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000034","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This rule targets typical behaviors used by suspicious and malicious add-ons and scripts (extensions) that create or launch executable files. This is a typical malware technique. Extensions will be blocked from being used by Office apps. Typically these extensions use the Windows Scripting Host (.wsh files) to run scripts that automate certain tasks or provide user-created add-on features.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213458","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213458","rule_id_src":"SV-213458r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDA869-6E2A-1014-B6E4-F0B5225CF049","group_id_src":"V-213458","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213458r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:34","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92667","V-77971"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000035","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word, Excel, or PowerPoint, will not be able to inject code into other processes. This is typically used by malware to run malicious code in an attempt to hide the activity from antivirus scanning engines.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213459","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213459","rule_id_src":"SV-213459r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDAC03-6E2A-1014-B41D-9BD99F019A39","group_id_src":"V-213459","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213459r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:35","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92669","V-77973"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D \nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000036","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"JavaScript and VBScript scripts can be used by malware to launch other malicious apps. This rule prevents these scripts from being allowed to launch apps, thus preventing malicious use of the scripts to spread malware and infect machines.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213460","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213460","rule_id_src":"SV-213460r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDB0F9-6E2A-1014-8085-A6F9F63A04E3","group_id_src":"V-213460","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213460r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:36","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92671","V-77975"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000037","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Malware and other threats can attempt to obfuscate or hide their malicious code in some script files. This rule prevents scripts that appear to be obfuscated from running. It uses the AntiMalwareScanInterface (AMSI) to determine if a script is potentially obfuscated and then blocks such a script or blocks scripts when an attempt is made to access them.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules4CC)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213461","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213461","rule_id_src":"SV-213461r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDB52F-6E2A-1014-9883-FE326DD091DB","group_id_src":"V-213461","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213461r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:37","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92673","V-77977"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000038","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This rule blocks potentially malicious behavior by not allowing macro code to execute routines in the Win 32 dynamic link library (DLL).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213462","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213462","rule_id_src":"SV-213462r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDB92A-6E2A-1014-BC98-9E961474C7B4","group_id_src":"V-213462","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213462r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:38","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92675","V-77979"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10, it is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" is set to \"Enabledâ and \"Block\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableNetworkProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Block\" in the drop-down box.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000039","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard network protection to prevent employees from using any application to access dangerous domains that may host phishing scams, exploit-hosting sites, and other malicious content on the internet.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\\Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213463","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213463","rule_id_src":"SV-213463r961092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDBCF6-6E2A-1014-A118-C66AF075D758","group_id_src":"V-213463","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213463r961092"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:40","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94669","V-79965"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Showâ¦\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"4\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"4\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"4\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000040","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-High)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213464","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213464","rule_id_src":"SV-213464r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDC0D4-6E2A-1014-828F-E41BF8F2F67E","group_id_src":"V-213464","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213464r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:41","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94671","V-79967"],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Showâ¦\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"2\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"2\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"2\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000041","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Medium)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213465","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213465","rule_id_src":"SV-213465r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDC49F-6E2A-1014-ADBC-CFB33485E8DA","group_id_src":"V-213465","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213465r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval: