t levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Low)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Low.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213466","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-213466","rule_id_src":"SV-213466r961086_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDC86C-6E2A-1014-882A-EF6823D4503F","group_id_src":"V-213466","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-213466r961086"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278647","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000043","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Adobe Reader from launching other processes, which can help mitigate security risks associated with malicious PDF files.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278647","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278647","rule_id_src":"SV-278647r1144030_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDCC64-6E2A-1014-84EB-957D7C7A1C50","group_id_src":"V-278647","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278647r114